FT  05 NOV 92 / Observer: Inn-tolerance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Only a few days after the French government started its anti-smoking drive,
the backlash has begun.
The sign on the door of a cafe in Saint-Germain reads: 'Reserve aux fumeurs.
Non-fumeurs acceptes'. Which roughly translated means: 'Smokers Only.
Non-smokers tolerated'.
