<TEXT>
EVIDENCE submitted to the Commons social security committee disclose just
part of the total professional fees charged so far by accountants and
lawyers in unravelling the Maxwell empire, Andrew Jack writes. They include:
Pounds 8m in legal fees and Pounds 7m from Price Waterhouse, administrators
to Maxwell Communication Corporation.
Pounds 5m in legal fees and Pounds 6m from Arthur Andersen, administrators
to MCC.
Pounds 2.1m in legal fees and Pounds 1.6m from Robson Rhodes, liquidators to
Bishopsgate Investment Management, manager and trustee of the Maxwell
pension funds.
Pounds 443,000 from Buchler Phillips, receivers to the estate of Robert
Maxwell.
