FT  05 NOV 92 / International Company News: Reynolds to make aluminium
vehicle parts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KENNETH GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
REYNOLDS Metals, third-largest of the world's aluminium groups, is to spend
Dollars 26m on a plant at Auburn, Indiana, to produce aluminium extruded
components for the automotive industry, writes Kenneth Gooding.
Technology for the components - bumper systems, door intrusion beams and
sun-roof tracks - was developed at Reynolds' Netherlands plant.
Several employees will be transferred from there to the new facility in the
US, due to start up late next year.
Reynolds and other western world aluminium companies see the automotive
industry as a key market.
Mr Richard Holder, chairman, said recently forecasts predicted the aluminium
content of the average US car would more than double in five years from
170lbs to 350lbs.
</TEXT>
