<HEADLINE>
FT  05 NOV 92 / International Company News: Rockwell hit by fall in sales
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LOS ANGELES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ROCKWELL International's operating net income for the fiscal fourth quarter
and year to end-September fell due to declining sales in several of its main
business segments, Reuter reports from Los Angeles.
Sales declined on the year for its electronics, aerospace, and graphics
segments, and fell for the quarter in aerospace and graphics, leaving only
automotive to post increased sales.
Rockwell reported net income of Dollars 138.1m, or Dollars 0.62 per share
for the fourth quarter against net income of Dollars 152.4m, or Dollars 0.66
per share, after a gain in the previous-year period.
It reported a fiscal year net loss of Dollars 1.04bn, or Dollars 4.62 per
share, after a charge of Dollars 6.78 per share on adoption of new
accounting rules for post-retirement benefits.
</TEXT>
