<HEADLINE>
FT  05 NOV 92 / International Company News: Paramount names heads of film
and TV activities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PARAMOUNT Pictures moved quickly to name a new studio head to replace Mr
Brandon Tartikoff, who resigned last week citing family obligations.
Ms Sherry Lansing, the best known woman in Hollywood film making, was
appointed to the newly created position of chairman of the Paramount's
motion picture group.
The 48-year-old Ms Lansing first made her name in the early 1980s when she
served for three years as president of production at 20th Century Fox.
Before that she had been a senior vice-president at Columbia Pictures.
Paramount said the appointment of Ms Lansing reflected a structural change
in the Paramount Pictures organisation.
Mr Tartikoff had previously headed both film and television activities. But
the company yesterday named Mr Kerry McCluggage as head of the television
division. Both he and Ms Lansing will report to Mr Stanley Jaffe, who is
president and chief operating officer of Paramount Communications, the
parent company.
Mr Jaffe is an old friend and business partner of Ms Lansing's. Until he
joined Paramount in March 1991, he and Ms Lansing had a joint film
production deal with Paramount called Jaffe/Lansing Productions.
Mr Elton John, the British-born pop star, has signed a publishing contract
estimated at Dollars 39m with Warner-Chappell Music, a division of Time
Warner. The 12-year deal includes the rights to all songs written since 1974
by Mr John and Mr Bernie Taupin, his collaborator, plus songs from the next
six albums.
