<HEADLINE>
FT  04 NOV 92 / Observer: If the cap fits
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It is a pity that the diminutive Texan multi-millionaire Ross Perot - a
feisty critic of the shortcomings of the North American Free Trade Agreement
(which he claims would create a 'huge sucking sound' of US manufacturing
jobs heading south to Mexico) - should be let down by the less than deeply
patriotic red-white-and-blue baseball cap which last week was being
distributed by his campaign team in Florida. 'Perot for President' it reads
on the outside; 'Produced for you in China' on the label inside.
</TEXT>
